<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM39300 &ndash; Taxation: Grant
of share options - general</h1>
<br>
<p>When an option is granted to an employee or director by reason
of an employment chargeable to tax under section 15 (earnings for
year when employee UK resident), no charge to income tax arises in
respect of the grant).
<br>
<br> If case law were followed, taxable earnings would arise only
on the grant of an option (Abbott v Philbin 39TC82 - see 
<a href="/ersmmanual/ersm110100.htm" target="_top">ERSM110100</a>);
however specific legislation at ICTA88/s135 and later in Chapter 5
of Part 7 Income Tax (Earnings and Pensions) Act 2003 overrides
this general rule in most cases.
<br>
<br> Section 135 ICTA 1988 overrides the effect of the decision
in Abbott v Philbin, for share options granted in respect of
employments within the old Case I of Schedule E. It</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">imposed a specific Schedule E charge on
gains realised by the exercise, assignment or release of such
options</li>
<li class="filledcircle">disapplied the Schedule E emoluments

charge on the grant of such options if they were not capable of

being exercised more than seven years (10 years for options granted

between 6/4/1998 &amp; 15/4/2003) after they were granted

(&ldquo;short options&rdquo;).</li>
</ul>
<p>The normal Schedule E emoluments charge under Section 19 ICTA

1988 was retained for grants of "long" options. The amount

chargeable was the &ldquo;money&rsquo;s worth&rdquo; of the option

on the date of grant less any consideration given for the grant.

Section 135(5) ICTA 1988 placed a minimum value on the option as

the extent to which the market value of the underlying shares at

the date of grant exceeds the option exercise price.

<br>
<br> In practice no Schedule E liability arose on the grant of

the share option if it was granted at a price equal to the market

value of the shares at the date of grant.

<br>
<br> These changes were incorporated into Chapter 5 of Part 7

ITEPA 2003 with one or two notable changes, in particular removing

the &ldquo;short&rdquo; &amp; &ldquo;long&rdquo; option

concepts.</p>
<br>
